{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 15:15:13.013219", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission accepted.\n\nSummary of what I submitted\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"host_1_1_1_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_static_blackhole\"]\n\nExplanation (short)\n- The diagnosis indicates an isolated endpoint failure: host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.10) is not reachable and not participating in reachability tests despite having an IP and a live interface.\n- This matches a host-local static blackhole (host dropping/ignoring traffic or otherwise not responding). Recommended follow-up: inspect host firewall, NIC/link, ARP entries, and capture traffic on the host and its access switch port.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2485, "output_tokens": 144, "total_tokens": 2629, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 0}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
